Bunge Receives Permit to Build Biodiesel Production Facility in Brazil

-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 
2011-04-26T19:18:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/bunge-receives-permit-to-build-biodiesel-production-facility-in-brazil.html
Bunge Alimentos SA, the Brazilian
unit of U.S. agricultural company  Bunge Ltd. (BG) , received a permit
to build a biodiesel manufacturing facility as the nation
increases its supply of the renewable fuel.  The plant in Mato Grosso state will be able to produce
414,800 liters (109,400 gallons) of biodiesel a day when
complete, fuel regulator Agencia Nacional do Petroleo, Gas
Natural e Biocombustiveis said today in  Brazil ’s official
 Gazette .  There are 60 biodiesel refineries with permits to sell fuel
in Brazil with total production capacity of 16.3 million liters
a year, according to the fuel regulator, known as  ANP . That’s up
from 47 at the start of 2010 when Brazil started enforcing a law
requiring diesel distributors to mix in 5 percent biodiesel with
their fuel, ANP said.  Bunge Alimentos produces  soybean oil , the most commonly
used biodiesel feedstock in Brazil, according to ANP.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 